I am being sweet to myself in my everyday yoga practice by closing the session with three gentle kisses on my hands - With the hands still drawn together, I give myself one little kiss on the roots of my hands,  one on the roots of my thumbs, and one on my thumbs. Just wanted to let you know that the word "Eskimo" is considered to be a racial slur by most peoples Indigenous to the Arctic. A helpful article on this can be found here: https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2016/04/24/475129558/why-you-probably-shouldnt-say-eskimo
 If you really want to reference affectionate nose-touching, the Inuit term is "kunik"! I think it's important to engage in other cultures with respect to their language and boundaries- that's something I love about how you teach yoga, so I thought you'd want to know. <3

Dear Adriene,   
I've been doing your videos for two years now.    On Nov 7th I suffered a serious fall while hiking and broke my proximal humerus (upper foreman) in two places and damaged my shoulder ligaments etc. and dislocated my should.      We don't discuss the brutal first 4 weeks- but once that part was over  I began slowly getting on my mat and doing whatever I could on my fav videos of yours. ( I went to physio therapy once but was so unhappy with the manual forcing of stretching I left in tears and refused to go back).     Today I saw my othropedic dr.     2.5 months in and he was amazed at my progress.   He went as far as suggesting that he hire me to consult with his patients for rehabilitiation as I've far exheeded anyone he's seen at the 3 month mark.  :)  ha ha .  He was just kidding but he gave me a A++++    I have to thank you-  I believe it's my past yoga practices with you.. every day for almost two years and my current ones- which I tailor to what my body can do.... just as you suggest to us... which has made me his star patient.   Might I add I'm  very young 60 year old!!!!  Blessings. to you.  and thanks.

Almost 2 years ago, I decided to start doing yoga to lose some weight and feel better. I didn‚Äôt have a specific goal in mind. I just knew that I needed to be in better shape and I really didn‚Äôt like how I felt in my skin. I started practicing Yoga with Adrienne on YouTube. I did yoga every day for 30 days. I started drinking more water, going for walks and eating smaller portions. I never weighed myself and still don‚Äôt. I felt like giving up and did not finish every practice, but I didn‚Äôt quit. After the 30 days, I kept going. I do yoga every day; some days are easy, some are difficult. I enjoy this practice because Adrienne will tell you to listen to your body and find what feels good. If you can‚Äôt go all the way today, then go half way and that‚Äôs okay!  Slowly I began to feel better. I started noticing I could walk and breathe better. I could chase around a kid and not feel like my legs were going to fall off. And yesterday, I bought a pair of pants in a size medium! I think the last time I was in a size medium was middle school. I‚Äôm not trying to be a certain size or be sexy or impress anyone. I just want to feel better. And I do. I hope my journey can help you and I send all of you positive thoughts.
